+# GitHub remote-publication boundary audit — 0276-r1
+
+## Existing surfaces
+
+- `github_publication_review.py`: bounded local review with pending/approve/revise/reject;
+- `source_candidate_remote_mutation_gate.py`: default-closed allowlist/operator gate;
+- `source_candidate_github_adapter.py`: plan/dry-run/apply protocol with fake-only implementation;
+- 0275-r5: pending publication preview carrying durable refs.
+
+## Required extension
+
+A real adapter must be a narrow transport membrane, not a global client. It must
+receive an approved review, durable SQL/final refs, policy decision, repository
+allowlist, expected remote revision and explicit operator confirmation.
+
+0276-r3 may implement stdlib HTTP transport but must refuse apply until a 0276-r4 preflight receipt proves revision, state, marker and replay safety.
+
+## First supported mutations
+
+- issue comment;
+- issue body update;
+- issue label replacement.
+
+ProjectV2 GraphQL mutation remains deferred until these REST paths are proven.
+
+## Locked failure modes
+
+- stale `updated_at` or ETag;
+- closed issue unless policy allows it;
+- deterministic publication marker already present;
+- desired labels already present (idempotent replay);
+- missing permissions or unexpected response schema;
+- token absent, empty or accidentally serialized.
